uotes, media shared on X, and Grok interactions).\n*   **Paid Subscribers (as of March 31, 2026):** ~6.3 million total active paid subscribers (~4.4 million X Premium/Premium+ and ~1.9 million Grok subscription tiers).\n\n### Caveats, Limitations, and Methodological Disclaimers\n\nThe text includes several important caveats about these metrics:\n\n1.  **MAU Definition & Calculation:**\n    *   **Definition:** MAU is the total number of **registered users** who interacted with Grok or X at least once in the past 30 days.\n    *   **De-duplication:** Users who access both platforms are identified via sign-in traffic to avoid double-counting in the combined figure.\n    *   **Important Limitation:** The company states: "While we believe our methodologies provide a reasonable approximation... they may not fully capture all instances of duplication, and our reported MAU should be viewed as **an estimate** of unique users."\n\n2.  **Daily Posts Definition:**\n    *   This metric includes all original posts, replies, reposts, quotes, media on X, **and** real-time interactions and generative capabilities provided by Grok. Notably, it "**may include posts generated by AI or accounts managed by AI**."\n\n3.  **Strategic Priority vs. MAU:**\n    *   The company explicitly states that while MAU provides an estimated measure of size and engagement, it is "focused on **revenue and operating margin**," and manages its business for sustainable revenue and profitability "rather than with the primary objective of growing or maintaining MAU levels."\n\n4.  **Volatility of Usage Metrics:**\n    *   In the Risk Factors section, it is noted that the consumer AI market is characterized by rapid iteration and intense competition. As a result, "**download and other usage metrics for any individual AI application, including Grok, can fluctuate significantly** (including periods of decreased Grok app downloads and user activity) in response to competitor model releases, product update cycles,