ment depth.\n*   The risk factors section notes that download and usage metrics for AI applications like Grok "can fluctuate significantly (including periods of decreased Grok app downloads and user activity)" due to competition and market dynamics, which speaks to variable but not necessarily casual engagement.\n\n**Regarding Conversion, Retention, and Monetization Metrics:**\n*   **Conversion to Paid Subscribers:** “As of March 31, 2026, we reached approximately 6.3 million active paid subscribers, which was comprised of approximately 4.4 million X Premium and Premium+ paid subscribers and approximately 1.9 million SuperGrok, SuperGrok Heavy and SuperGrok Lite paid subscribers.”\n*   **Monetization Strategy:**\n    *   **Advertising:** “We also monetize user activity through high-impact advertising inventory on X.” The strategy focuses on growing advertising revenue per user through AI-driven targeting and integration.\n    *   **Subscriptions:** The strategy includes “converting a greater portion of our user base into paying subscribers” for both X and Grok offerings.\n*   **Retention Factors (implied):**\n    *   A stated goal is to “increase retention” by strengthening ad product performance and relevance.\n    *   The continuous release of “increasingly capable Grok models” and new features is intended to “increase the penetration rate of our subscriber base” and support long-term growth, implying a focus on ongoing value delivery for retention.',
